"},{"id":681,"type":"Other fraudulent behaviour","victim":"| steamname: FLAIM | steam3ID: [U:1:144725661] | steamID32: STEAM_0:1:72362830 | steamID64: http://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561198104991389 | customURL: http://steamcommunity.com/id/ | steamrep: http://steamrep.com/profiles/76561198104991389 ","accused":"76561198233331152 (Davey Wavey)","description":"On January 23, I was added by a guy called "Reptinguru" (now named Davey Wavey), who offered me a duped Stormy 13th Hour Safe n sound for my duped Sunbeams Nappers Respite. After talking to some friends about the Safe n Sound price I decided to ask Davey to add. He offered to add a starstorm insomnia chicken hat, but I had my eye on his Stattrak Factory New M4A4 Griffin with 4 of the 2014 Cologne Cloud 9 Holo stickers on it. I asked Davey if he would be willing to do all 3 for my Nappers, and he said the m4a4 was not tradable yet. I thought about it, and decided that his backpack was big enough that id be able to trust him to deliver it on the date it was tradable. (he had well over $500usd in both his csgo and tf2 backpack) I proposed the idea to Davey, and he agreed saying "I'd be willing to do that". (Reference Screenshot: ReptinguruDaveyScam4). I was happy that he was willing to do it, so I wanted to give him a little something in return, but he said the trade would be fine without any additional adds on my side. I again reassured that he would give me the M4A4, and asked the date when itd become tradable. Which he replied with "yup" and "jan 27", so I decided that Davey would hold his word and give me the m4a4 on January 27. January 27 comes, and I message Davey hello, and tell him that ive sent an offer for the m4a4. Davey declined the offer, and despite multiple messages throughout the day, he refused to reply back. This morning (Jan 28) Davey replied back, saying that he did nothing wrong, and that he refuses to hold the trade agreement. I offered to drop the whole thing if he would just sell it to me for a reasonable price. He originally started by asking for 6 csgo pure or 8 in tf2 items. I tried to fullfill the 8 in items but he changed his mind saying he wanted 6-7 in csgo items. I offered a bit over 7 in csgo items, and he wanted another pure key on top of that, so i just decided to offer him his original 6 pure asking price. Then all the sudden he magically remembered there were stickers on there (that I had previously made huge efforts stressing thats why I wanted the m4 so bad) and said he wanted 12 pure. I offered 10, and he accepted the offer. SO, not only did he completely lie about the fact that the m4a4 was supposed to be FREE as part of the nappers trade, he abused the fact that he knew how badly I wanted it to up his price to 10 keys. So at the end of the day, I was robbed out of 10 CS:GO Glove keys, and Davey refuses to believe he did anything wrong, when he blatantly lied about our trade agreement, and did not fullfill it. I never want Davey to have the satisfaction of lying to someone else again.
